Netcare911 says reports from the scene indicate that gas was being used in the scrapyard when the fire broke out. JOHANNESBURG Thirteen people have been injured in a scrapyard fire in Doornfontein on Thursday afternoon.Netcare911 says reports from the scene indicate that gas was being used in the scrapyard when the fire broke out.Scrap yard fire in centra Johannesburg leaves 2 critical, 9 serious and 2 with minor injuries @JacaNews @ewnupdates @News24 @Beeld_NuusIt's understood two people are in a critical condition while seven others sustained serious injuries.Netcare911's Chris Botha says, The paramedics from Netcare 911 and the provincial ambulances stabilised the patients and then transported to various hospitals in the area where they are receiving treatment at the moment. 